  "text": "Example 3: The problem is further illustrated by means of an example. A rule from some guideline document may be \"Avoid passive voice.\". By making use of typed dependencies it can easily be checked whether a sentence is given in active or passive voice since different relations are found in the corresponding typed dependency graphs. While the subject is indicated as the dependent of a 'nsubj' relation in a sentence in active voice the relation will be 'nsubjpass' when using passive voice (cf. Fig. 3 ). But it cannot only be checked rather easy whether the rule is violated by inspecting whether such dependency relations occur in the sentence; passive sentences can also be translated automatically using NLP techniques. [CITATION_1] ",
